S Subparts A, B, C, D, E, F, and G (Reserved) 1. The authority citation for part 507 continues to read as follows: Authority: 8 U.S.C. 1101(a)(15)(H)(i)(b), 1182(n), and 1184, and 29 U.S.C. 49 et seq. ; and Pub. L. 102&hyph;232, 105 stat. 1733, 1748 (8 U.S.C. 1182 note). Subparts H and I [Revised] 2. Part 507 is amended by revising subparts H and I to read as set forth at the end of the common preamble. Subpart H_Labor Condition Applications and Requirements for Employers Using Nonimmigrants on H&hyph;1B Visas in Specialty Occupations and as Fashion Models Sec. 507.700␣Purpose, procedure and applicability of subparts H and I of this part. 507.705␣Overview of responsibilities. 507.710␣Complaints. 507.715␣Definitions. 507.720␣Addresses of Department of Labor regional offices. 507.730␣Labor condition application. 507.731␣The first labor condition statement: wages.
